{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:12:12.756233+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 9a7ab4a43b359ce089e5b88c4f6f7515daa7431c)", "id": "lc_9ef30ab3-9f81-406b-a0fa-7a857c56615d"}, {"type": "text", "text": "CREATE TABLE sessions (\n    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY,\n    user_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    issued_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    expires_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL\n);\n", "id": "lc_cc41ffd8-6a56-4602-8d24-77f4d1266b25"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "12185330-e99d-4363-862e-09b790ebb573", "tool_call_id": "call_7665d8c3cf7e485c9a0dc65d", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:12:29.312386+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "There are three database migration files in the `migrations/` directory. They would be applied in numerical order: `001`, `002`, and `003`. \n\nHere is what each one does:\n\n1. **`001_create_users.sql`**\n   - **Creates the `users` table.** This is the foundational table for user accounts. It sets up columns for:\n     - `id`: A unique, auto-incrementing primary key (`BIGSERIAL`).\n     - `email`: A unique, non-null text field for user email addresses.\n     - `display_name`: An optional text field for a user's name.\n     - `created_at`: A timestamp that defaults to the current time upon creation.\n\n2. **`002_create_sessions.sql`**\n   - **Creates the `sessions` table.** This table is used to manage user login sessions. It includes:\n     - `id`: A `UUID` used as the primary key.\n     - `user_id`: A foreign key that links the session to a user in the `users` table. The `ON DELETE CASCADE` ensures that if a user is deleted, their sessions are also automatically removed.\n     - `issued_at`: A timestamp for when the session was created.\n     - `expires_at`: A timestamp indicating when the session expires.\n\n3. **`003_add_session_index.sql`**\n   - **Adds an index to the `sessions` table.** Specifically, it creates an index on the `user_id` column. This is a performance optimization to speed up database queries that look up sessions by a specific user (e.g., \"find all active sessions for user X\").", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 477, "prompt_tokens": 5924, "total_tokens": 6401, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 123, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 5696, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0005346756, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001196856, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00041499}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780963933-uiknkhZWeUvDfPoOdkKj", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9b8-fa54-7a60-ba81-32aa8b67c993-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5924, "output_tokens": 477, "total_tokens": 6401, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 5696}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 123}}}}]}}}
